  "text": "Haplotype and linkage analysis. SIMWALK version 2.83 [CITATION_1] as implemented at the U.K. Medical Research Council Human Genome Mapping Project Computing Centre (http://www.rfcgr. mrc.ac.uk/Registered/Menu/link-gen.html) was used for data cleaning and maximum likelihood estimation of microsatellite haplotypes unconstrained by phenotypic data. Multiple program runs were performed to confirm the stability and robustness of haplotype assignment. The patterns of haplotype transmission were then examined to determine the haplotypes shared by affected individuals and not shared by unaffected individuals within each family. This was undertaken under each of two phenotypic models.",
